    "body": "### Problem\r\n\r\nI'm just starting with Neovim and I started with :help and then :Tutor. \r\nIt explains in good details which keys to press to navigate the text. But when I got to the editing, it just says \"Sometimes you will be required to modify text\" and expect me to somehow modify the next line. I have no idea how to do this at this point. I've tried pressing Enter and typing, I've tried navigating to highlighted links Enter and `like this`, I've tried using :help and found :append command (but after entering it, I couldn't exit it, no matter how many times I typed :q).\r\n![image](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/assets/39321074/02abe549-0f31-4913-bfba-43a208ce4624)\r\n\r\n\r\n### Expected behavior\r\n\r\nI expect the Tutor would say how to modify a text before expecting me to be able to do it.",
